			<title><![CDATA[Jared Yates Sexton: Trump's Death Cult, American Mythology, White Supremacy and Deadly Denialism]]></title>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>In an interview recorded May 18, writer and political analyst Jared Yates Sexton discusses Trump’s death cult with activist Sam Goldman. Jared Yates Sexton is an author and political analyst whose work has appeared in <em>The New York Times</em>, <em>The New Republic</em>, <em>Politico</em>, <em>The Daily Beast</em>, and elsewhere. Most recently he’s the author of <em>American Rule: How A Nation Conquered The World But Failed Its People</em>, forthcoming from Dutton/Penguin-Random House in Fall 2020. He can be found on Twitter <a href="https://twitter.com/jysexton?lang=en">@jysexton</a> and hosts The Muckrake podcast. Read his latest piece, <em>Deus Vult: Donald Trump and America's Holy War Threaten Everything</em> We Know at <a href="https://www.themuckrake.com/main/new-crusade">TheMuckrake.com</a>. Then, Sarah Roark, Co-Editor of <a href="https://refusefascism.org/2020/06/16/why-we-cant-wait-for-november/">RefuseFascism.org</a> talks about whether we can or should wait until the November elections to remove Trump. Follow Sarah's political writings at <a href="https://refusefascism.org/2020/06/16/why-we-cant-wait-for-november/">RefuseFascism.org</a> and follow her on Twitter <a href="https://twitter.com/afterdaylight?lang=en">@afterdaylight</a>.</p>
